      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "UNRWA USA's operational strength lies in its ability to scale rapidly during humanitarian emergencies. Between 2021 and 2023, the organization achieved a <cite id=\"12\">3-year revenue CAGR of 113.8%</cite>, demonstrating a robust capacity to mobilize resources. Their governance is supported by an <cite id=\"13\">independent board of 13 members</cite>, ensuring oversight and strategic alignment. Furthermore, their <cite id=\"14\">working capital of 3.9 months</cite> provides a resilient buffer for ongoing operations in volatile regions."
      ],
      "summary": "UNRWA USA National Committee serves as a critical lifeline for Palestine refugees, focusing on human development and emergency humanitarian relief. The organization has demonstrated remarkable growth, reporting <cite id=\"1\">$32,433,934 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 fiscal year, a significant increase that highlights its expanding role in crisis response. Operating with a <cite id=\"2\">93.4% program expense ratio</cite>, the charity ensures that every dollar of its functional expenses is dedicated to its core mission, which includes <cite id=\"3\">education, food assistance, and health services</cite>. Their work is primarily focused on the <cite id=\"4\">Gaza Strip, West Bank, and Lebanon</cite>, where they provide essential services to a population facing chronic instability. The organization maintains a <cite id=\"5\">95.5/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite>, reflecting a high standard of institutional accountability. Beyond direct aid, UNRWA USA aims to <cite id=\"6\">reshape the narrative around Palestine refugees</cite> in the United States, advocating for their dignity and rights. Their financial model is highly efficient, requiring only <cite id=\"7\">$0.05 to raise every $1</cite>, which is well below industry averages for humanitarian organizations. This efficiency, combined with a <cite id=\"8\">verified zakat-eligible status</cite>, makes it a primary choice for Muslim donors seeking to support Palestinian communities through established, large-scale infrastructure.",
